This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and machine translation. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes domain-adaptation techniques, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the obfuscation of gender traits in translations, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper mentions the use of original texts and translations, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound).
